This paper deals with monitoring and analyzing network traffic flows, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses anomaly detection, which is a common topic in computer security (cs.CR). The use of complex network theory and statistical analysis also suggests a potential fit for the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
